1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,338
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,551 --> 00:00:12,721
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:16,516 --> 00:00:17,517
[Atoy] <i>What are you doing here?</i>

4
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:21,604
[Ibyang] <i>Why are you hiding</i>
<i>things like this here?</i>

5
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:25,191
You have money.
Why don't you fix the shop?

6
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:29,738
Promise me you won't tell anyone
you saw this room.

7
00:00:29,821 --> 00:00:35,243
[Ibyang] Just save my Big Sister Ame,
and I'll forget everything about you.

8
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:36,244
Mmm-hmm.

9
00:00:36,327 --> 00:00:38,913
- [thudding]
- [crowd cheering]

10
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:40,874
- [Bebang] Ma'am Lorna wants to see you.
- [bell dinging]

11
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:44,127
[Bebang] <i>There's a big-time customer</i>
<i>who wants to meet you.</i>

12
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:48,173
[in English] I have a client in Japan,
and he would absolutely love you.

13
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,090
PREVIOUSLY

14
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:50,925
[in English] All you have to do
is make him happy,

15
00:00:51,009 --> 00:00:53,052
and he will change your life!

16
00:00:53,762 --> 00:00:54,512
What?

17
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:57,599
Looks like Ame was forced
into underground fighting.

18
00:00:57,682 --> 00:00:59,225
- What?!
- [Atoy] <i>But don't worry.</i>

19
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:01,352
[Atoy] <i>I already have a way to get inside.</i>

20
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:02,896
[Atoy] <i>Can you do my makeup again?</i>

21
00:01:02,979 --> 00:01:03,980
What's your peg this time?

22
00:01:05,982 --> 00:01:06,816
Um, ma'am.

23
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:07,734
Oh?

24
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:12,405
I heard you made
a killing again last night, huh?

25
00:01:12,489 --> 00:01:13,990
[both chuckling]

26
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:15,617
What kind of rumor is that?

27
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:17,202
[Bebang chuckles]

28
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:18,453
[man 2] Don't deny it.

29
00:01:18,536 --> 00:01:20,747
We're not going to ask you
to treat us anyway.

30
00:01:20,830 --> 00:01:21,831
That's right.

31
00:01:22,332 --> 00:01:24,918
And don't keep it from us.

32
00:01:25,627 --> 00:01:29,798
Because we know you get a big cut here.

33
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:31,090
[both chuckling]

34
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:32,675
It's just enough.

35
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:36,638
You know I can't demand much
from Ma'am Lorna,

36
00:01:36,721 --> 00:01:39,516
even though I was the one who found Ame.

37
00:01:40,809 --> 00:01:42,185
[Bebang] Even better.

38
00:01:42,685 --> 00:01:46,856
The Japanese like good-looking dwarfs!

39
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,483
[man 1] Oh, really? [laughs]

40
00:01:48,566 --> 00:01:50,860
A peculiar kind of pervert, huh?

41
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:51,861
[men laugh]

42
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:54,155
[man 1] You know, Bebang,
you're still lucky.

43
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:56,366
So, when will you get your cut?

44
00:01:56,449 --> 00:01:57,534
[Bebang] Tonight.

45
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:02,664
When the Japanese man picks her up
with a private plane.

46
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:04,499
[Bebang chuckles]

47
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:06,459
[man 1] Hey. Bebang.

48
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:07,544
[Bebang] What?

49
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,212
[man 1] Share some.

50
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,506
[upbeat music playing]

51
00:02:11,589 --> 00:02:13,424
[clicking and clacking]

52
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:15,635
[electronic blipping]

53
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:20,640
[upbeat music playing]

54
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:41,494
- [phone buttons beeping]
- [line rings]

55
00:02:41,578 --> 00:02:42,620
[Atoy, in English] Hello, sir.

56
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:44,414
I need to borrow a car from you.

57
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:47,667
Something… a bit retro.

58
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:50,378
So, you know Emerson?

59
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:52,088
- Hmm.
- [somber music playing]

60
00:02:52,171 --> 00:02:53,923
He used to work with my father.

61
00:02:54,757 --> 00:02:59,304
But he was poaching clients,
so he got fired.

62
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:01,639
So, don't trust him, okay?!

63
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:05,310
Maybe he just really needed it.

64
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:06,561
Even so.

65
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:09,814
No matter how you twist it,
what he did was wrong!

66
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:14,652
No. I feel like he's a good person.

67
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:16,237
[somber music playing]

68
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:17,989
Why? Do you like Emerson?

69
00:03:18,072 --> 00:03:20,909
Hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm!

70
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:23,953
Of course not. You're disgusting!

71
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:26,831
[quirky music playing]

72
00:03:28,374 --> 00:03:31,127
After this, Tonet, you can go home.

73
00:03:32,670 --> 00:03:34,339
‪[Atoy chuckles softly]

74
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:37,008
[Atoy] What's that?

75
00:03:37,592 --> 00:03:39,469
[Karla] Bro Atoy. You wanted to see me?

76
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:44,265
Are you going to make me
babysit that brat again?

77
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:46,100
I don't want to!
I'll get dragged into trouble again!

78
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:47,560
[thrilling music playing]

79
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:48,853
No.

80
00:03:48,937 --> 00:03:50,647
I have something else for you to do.

81
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:53,066
Are you ready?

82
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,194
How are your driving skills?

83
00:03:57,278 --> 00:04:00,365
I'm can't do Tokyo Drift, but I'm okay.

84
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:01,449
Get ready.

85
00:04:01,532 --> 00:04:02,825
Boom!

86
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:05,536
You're a driver, wearing white,
with gloves, with a hat.

87
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:09,707
[suave music playing]

88
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:10,667
[sewing machine whirring]

89
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:11,626
[swishing]

90
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:12,585
[snipping]

91
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:15,588
[sewing machine whirring]

92
00:04:15,672 --> 00:04:17,507
[sewing machine whirring]

93
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:20,885
[gun firing]

94
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:23,179
[clicking]

95
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:25,265
[snips]

96
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:29,143
[electronic blipping]

97
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:56,963
[upbeat Cuban-style music playing]

98
00:04:58,214 --> 00:05:00,091
<i>Buenas noches, señor!</i>

99
00:05:00,174 --> 00:05:06,306
[Cuban-style music continues]

100
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:23,489
This mission is a win, Big Bro Atoy!

101
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:27,827
Chipper Arenas. Huh?

102
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:29,203
That's the name you should remember.

103
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:31,664
Chipper Arenas. Okay, Carlotta?

104
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,750
Oh, right!

105
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:36,210
That's my code name.

106
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,172
[clears throat]

107
00:05:39,255 --> 00:05:41,007
Just make sure you take care of the car.

108
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:43,509
I just borrowed it from my boss.

109
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:45,261
[in English] Yes, Sir Chipper.

110
00:05:45,887 --> 00:05:47,680
And most importantly…

111
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:51,934
Make sure no one recognizes you.

112
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:53,227
[in English] Sir, yes, sir!

113
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:55,271
Don't worry.

114
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:57,273
My crew doesn't come here.

115
00:05:57,356 --> 00:05:58,733
This is for DOMs.

116
00:05:58,816 --> 00:06:01,944
- [whimsical flourish]
- [Cuban-style music continues]

117
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,863
[in English] Good evening, sir.
Welcome back!

118
00:06:03,946 --> 00:06:05,198
This way.

119
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:08,618
[Cuban-style music continues]

120
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:10,661
[car door clicks shut]

121
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:20,797
[in English] Sir, this way.

122
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:21,881
[Atoy] Mmm-hmm.

123
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:25,927
[energetic club music playing]

124
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:33,476
[in English] Hi, sir, good evening.

125
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:35,061
- Hey.
- [in English] I'll take it from here.

126
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:40,024
[in English] Um, sir,
would you like to see our girls?

127
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:42,276
We have fresh catch.

128
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:44,445
Very young

129
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:46,280
and ready for break-in.

130
00:06:47,323 --> 00:06:48,783
[in English] My dear…

131
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:51,244
[in English] I've had enough of that.

132
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:53,788
Oh…

133
00:06:54,288 --> 00:06:56,499
So you're looking for something else.

134
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:02,839
Well, perfect.
We have a great fight tonight.

135
00:07:02,922 --> 00:07:04,882
I'm sure you'll enjoy it, sir.

136
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,592
[in English] Please.

137
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:08,719
[Atoy, in English] Well, I really hope so.

138
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:10,847
[in English] I want to be entertained.

139
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:12,557
[in English] Sure, sir.

140
00:07:14,725 --> 00:07:15,935
[in English] Enjoy, sir.

141
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:20,940
[energetic club music playing]

142
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:36,873
[brazen music playing]

143
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:38,833
[electronic blipping]

144
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:42,044
[in English] Welcome, sir.

145
00:07:43,796 --> 00:07:49,427
[brazen music continues]

146
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:54,932
[in English] I cannot wait
to get my hands on Ame.

147
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:57,518
[in English] I made arrangements already.
You're gonna have her.

148
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:00,021
- [in English] Let's enjoy the fight first.
- [in English] Let's.

149
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:08,112
[menacing music playing]

150
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:17,705
[electronic blipping]

151
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:24,170
[crowd cheering]

152
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:29,175
[energetic club music playing]

153
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:40,686
[Bebang, in English] Good evening, boss!

154
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:43,105
Please sit down. Sit down.

155
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:45,316
[chuckles] You know, boss…

156
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:49,445
our next fight is quite exciting.

157
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:52,907
Two former friends,
now angry at each other.

158
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:53,824
[chuckles]

159
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:57,036
If you want to bet, just tell me.

160
00:08:57,703 --> 00:08:58,746
I'm your man, boss!

161
00:08:58,829 --> 00:09:02,500
[John] I recommended her to Bebang,
the "talent manager".

162
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:04,710
They talked about the gig themselves.

163
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:06,921
- [camera shutter clicking]
- <i>But I don't know if it pushed through.</i>

164
00:09:07,004 --> 00:09:07,838
‪[tense music playing]

165
00:09:09,423 --> 00:09:10,299
[in English] My dear…

166
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:11,467
[clears throat]

167
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:15,346
[in English] I want to put all my money

168
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:19,850
on this fighter who's well-known
among my acquaintances.

169
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:23,104
- Uh-huh.
- Amazing Ame.

170
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:24,564
Ah! [chuckles]

171
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:26,566
She's really famous!

172
00:09:26,649 --> 00:09:28,025
Too famous, actually.

173
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,528
[cackling]

174
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:33,406
Too bad, she has no more fights.

175
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:35,157
Her last fight was last night.

176
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:38,578
[stirring music playing]

177
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:39,787
Why?

178
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:40,997
Uh…

179
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:42,832
Did something happen to her?

180
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,251
No.

181
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:49,589
[in English] That's too bad. [sighs]

182
00:09:50,673 --> 00:09:51,674
[in English] 'Cause you know…

183
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,051
I really want to…

184
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:56,053
I only want to meet her.

185
00:09:56,137 --> 00:09:58,139
[stirring music continues]

186
00:09:58,222 --> 00:10:00,057
Maybe I could…

187
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,268
take a picture with her.

188
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:04,854
[Bebang] Hmm…

189
00:10:04,937 --> 00:10:06,480
Of course, boss!

190
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:08,149
No problem.

191
00:10:10,526 --> 00:10:12,820
I'll take care of it.
I'll get back to you.

192
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:14,572
All right.

193
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:16,782
‪[energetic club music playing]

194
00:10:21,078 --> 00:10:22,163
[in English] Here, man.

195
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:23,664
[in English] Okay, thank you.

196
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:24,874
[Red grunts]

197
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:28,836
- [energetic club music playing]
- [Vladimir groans]

198
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,256
Bring my bottle keep here, okay.

199
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,925
[in English] Hey, you. What do you want
to eat? You wanna eat something?

200
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:41,390
[stirring music playing]

201
00:10:43,517 --> 00:10:45,519
[Karla] You're awesome, babe.

202
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:48,189
Don't worry.

203
00:10:48,272 --> 00:10:50,399
[in English] You're in good hands
with Carlotta.

204
00:10:54,528 --> 00:10:56,072
[man, in English] Ah! Bro,
you're looking good.

205
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,239
- [in English] Let's go!
- [Jason] Whoo!

206
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:01,827
Are you sure?
This is where you want to go?

207
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:02,787
[Jason, in English] Dude, chill.

208
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:04,580
[in English] Don't tell me you
haven't been here before.

209
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:08,501
[man] Perfect!
This is your initiation, bro! Let's go!

210
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,504
If you want, you guys go ahead.

211
00:11:11,587 --> 00:11:13,339
[in English] Are you serious, Gav?

212
00:11:13,422 --> 00:11:14,673
[in English] What's wrong with you, bro?

213
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:16,342
I just don't like this, Jason.

214
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:18,677
But you guys go ahead. I'll stay here.

215
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:21,806
- You're so weird, bro!
- Come on! It's fine.

216
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:23,349
- [in English] Let's go!
- [in English] Game, bro.

217
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:24,183
- [in English] Let's go!
- [in English] Let's go!

218
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:25,184
[Jason] Take care!

219
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:39,824
[inquisitive music playing]

220
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:45,413
[in English] Wow!

221
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:51,961
Awesome!

222
00:11:53,087 --> 00:11:55,464
This is a V8 engine with 200 horsepower.

223
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:56,841
Is that right, miss?

224
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:02,138
Yes, V8 engine, 200 horsepower!

225
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:05,015
[mischievous music playing]

226
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:06,016
[scoffs]

227
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,810
I knew it!

228
00:12:07,893 --> 00:12:09,937
I recognize your voice, miss.

229
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:12,064
You're the one we played
basketball with us, right?

230
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:14,733
[in English] Basketball?

231
00:12:15,693 --> 00:12:17,445
That wasn't me, no.

232
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:19,238
I didn't play yesterday.

233
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:21,657
Ha! It was you!

234
00:12:23,242 --> 00:12:24,452
- Oh, ouch, ouch, ouch!
- Yes!

235
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:25,494
It was me!

236
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,705
- Ouch!
- [grunts in frustration]

237
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:32,293
And you were with that crazy guy
causing trouble in our barangay!

238
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:34,837
- [mischievous music continues]
- [grunts]

239
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:38,507
- [bell dings]
- [crowd cheering, clapping]

240
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:39,758
‪[upbeat club music playing]

241
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,678
[in English] Yes! Give it to him!

242
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,222
[in English] That's how you do it!

243
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:47,057
- [in English] Let's go!
- [crowd cheering]

244
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:48,976
[in English] Another one! Another one!

245
00:12:49,059 --> 00:12:52,062
[crowd cheering, whistling, clapping]

246
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:54,315
[in English] That's how you finish him!

247
00:12:54,815 --> 00:12:55,649
[in English] Very good!

248
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:58,611
[unsettling music playing]

249
00:12:58,694 --> 00:13:01,530
- [MC, in English] <i>We have a winner!</i>
- [bell dinging]

250
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:04,617
<i>Empacho Libre!</i>

251
00:13:04,700 --> 00:13:07,203
[crowd cheering clapping]

252
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:10,080
[somber music playing]

253
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:19,465
How are you, Ame?

254
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:22,426
Uh…

255
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:25,429
I don't have a fight today, Darryl.
They're letting me rest.

256
00:13:26,388 --> 00:13:27,640
You need to eat.

257
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:29,433
You need to get stronger.

258
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:33,896
[somber music playing]

259
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:36,106
I heard Bebang earlier.

260
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:40,694
They said you'll be taken tonight
to be sold to a customer.

261
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:45,824
[somber music continues]

262
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:49,161
Darryl, I don't want to.
I don't want to go!

263
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,371
[sighs]

264
00:13:50,454 --> 00:13:52,039
What will I do?

265
00:13:52,706 --> 00:13:53,999
I might never see Ibyang again!

266
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,751
They might kill me!

267
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:58,587
That's why you need to get stronger.

268
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:03,592
If I win my fight tonight,
I'll take you with me.

269
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:06,887
I don't know how yet.

270
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,514
But we'll escape.

271
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:13,227
[somber music continues]

272
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:15,854
[in English] This is the best thing
I've ever seen, Red!

273
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:17,398
- [in English] I love it!
- [in English] Sure.

274
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:19,775
[in English] I told you it's better
than Pacquiao, right?

275
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:20,734
[in English] Well…

276
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,612
[in English] Come
to think of it, not quite.

277
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:25,364
- [scoffs]
- [in English] Okay.

278
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:26,991
[in English] How about
we try something different?

279
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:29,326
[in English] What are you thinking?

280
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:30,578
[in English] Come here.

281
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:38,043
[in English] Interesting.

282
00:14:39,461 --> 00:14:41,046
- [in English] Okay. See what I can do.
- [in English] Yeah?

283
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:43,549
- [in English] I love it!
- [in English] I trust you.

284
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:46,385
[attendant, in English] Sir.

285
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:53,350
[MC, in English] <i>Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

286
00:14:54,602 --> 00:15:00,190
[in English] <i>We have prepared</i>
<i>a very special event for all of you.</i>

287
00:15:01,066 --> 00:15:05,529
[in English] <i>An event</i>
<i>that will surely satisfy your hunger</i>

288
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:08,240
<i>for blood and gore!</i>

289
00:15:08,949 --> 00:15:13,954
[in English] <i>Now let's call on two</i>
<i>of our strongest fighters of all time…</i>

290
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:17,416
<i>Darryl and Tessie!</i>

291
00:15:17,499 --> 00:15:21,253
[crowd cheering, clapping]

292
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:23,172
[in English] <i>This time, though,</i>

293
00:15:23,964 --> 00:15:27,384
<i>they will not be fighting each other.</i>

294
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:29,637
[in English] <i>This time,</i>

295
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:34,892
<i>they will be fighting two</i>
<i>of our most beloved</i>

296
00:15:34,975 --> 00:15:37,061
<i>patrons!</i>

297
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:40,648
[crowd cheering, clapping]

298
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:44,360
[menacing music playing]

299
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:51,408
We're at a disadvantage here!

300
00:15:51,492 --> 00:15:53,827
We have no choice, Tessie.

301
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:55,746
Let's just help each other.

302
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:57,247
All right.

303
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:05,547
[menacing music continues]

304
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:09,218
‪[somber music playing]

305
00:16:13,597 --> 00:16:14,431
Ame.

306
00:16:15,015 --> 00:16:16,183
What do you want?

307
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:18,352
There's a customer who wants
to take a picture with you.

308
00:16:18,435 --> 00:16:19,269
Come on!

309
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:22,231
N-no! I don't want to!
I won't go out there.

310
00:16:22,314 --> 00:16:25,442
Are you camera shy, girl? Come on!

311
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:27,277
Don't give me any problems! Come on!

312
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:28,529
- No, I said I don't want to!
- [unsettling music playing]

313
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:30,155
I know you're going to sell me!

314
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:32,074
- [man] What an imagination you have!
- [Bebang] Oh! Come on!

315
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:33,158
- [man] Stop acting up!
- I don't want to!

316
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:35,285
- I don't want to. Let me go!
- [Bebang] Come on.

317
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:36,745
- I don't want to!
- [Bebang] Hurry up!

318
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:38,914
[Ame] Let me go!

319
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:41,250
- [man] There, fine.
- [Ame] Let me go!

320
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:42,876
[Ame] Take your hands off me!

321
00:16:43,752 --> 00:16:46,046
[crowd cheering, clapping]

322
00:16:48,465 --> 00:16:51,051
[unsettling music playing]

323
00:16:55,848 --> 00:16:57,975
[Ame] What, what?!

324
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:59,143
What's going on?!

325
00:17:00,644 --> 00:17:03,355
[crowd cheering]

326
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:05,816
- [tense music playing]
- [cackles]

327
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:10,154
[tense music continues]

328
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:14,908
What the hell?! What are you doing?

329
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:17,036
Do I need to explain again?

330
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,204
- Do you want me to repeat it?
- [quirky music playing]

331
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:21,123
You looked like you could be nice,

332
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:23,709
but you're actually
a disciple of darkness!

333
00:17:24,209 --> 00:17:27,046
You don't even know me,
yet you're judging me already!

334
00:17:27,671 --> 00:17:29,173
Yes, I'm a judger!

335
00:17:29,256 --> 00:17:30,716
You're Mongki's man, aren't you?

336
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:32,217
What are you talking about?

337
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:33,844
He's my dad's man!

338
00:17:33,927 --> 00:17:36,889
Exactly. You're all disciples of darkness!

339
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:38,223
[grunting]

340
00:17:39,516 --> 00:17:40,976
I'm not like my dad!

341
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:43,145
[scoffs] And you?

342
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:44,563
What are you doing here?

343
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:47,483
Isn't it obvious?

344
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:49,818
I'm working as a driver.

345
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:52,571
For whom, a drug lord?

346
00:17:52,654 --> 00:17:54,907
A corrupt contractor? Oh!

347
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,576
So, we're all the same here.

348
00:17:57,659 --> 00:17:59,995
Because those kinds of people,
they're the patrons here.

349
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:02,081
He's not a drug lord.

350
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,458
And definitely not a corrupt contractor.

351
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:06,627
Yuck! I don't like those kinds of people!

352
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:07,878
Oh, so what is he then?

353
00:18:07,961 --> 00:18:09,171
That's none of your business!

354
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:10,631
There's no decent person here anyway.

355
00:18:10,714 --> 00:18:12,508
I said, that's none of your business.

356
00:18:13,592 --> 00:18:14,426
And you?

357
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,845
Why don't you want to join
your crew inside?

358
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,099
- Are you gay?
- [scoffs]

359
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:21,892
You're deaf too, huh?

360
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:24,019
I already said there's
no decent person there!

361
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:28,732
[curious music playing]

362
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:32,236
[crowd cheering]

363
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:34,113
[intense music playing]

364
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:35,030
[thuds]

365
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:37,116
- [grunts]
- [thuds]

366
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:40,035
What's this? Why are you allowing this?

367
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:42,913
You know they're at a huge disadvantage
in that fight!

368
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:44,790
What do you want, a subtitute, huh?

369
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:45,833
Replace Tessie?

370
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,503
- [thuds]
- [grunts]

371
00:18:49,586 --> 00:18:50,587
- [thuds]
- [grunts]

372
00:18:52,297 --> 00:18:53,340
[chuckles]

373
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:59,096
What I want is for you to stop
this cruelty you're doing to us!

374
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:00,722
We're people too!

375
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:03,183
You know, you're so dramatic!

376
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,351
Why don't you just be an actress?

377
00:19:06,436 --> 00:19:07,604
[thud]

378
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:08,939
[crowd cheering]

379
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:11,692
[intense music continues]

380
00:19:11,775 --> 00:19:14,444
[thudding]

381
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:20,784
[grunting]

382
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:23,495
- [gasping]
- That's what you deserve, you animals!

383
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:25,455
- [cackles]
- [grunting]

384
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:27,958
[loud grunt]

385
00:19:28,792 --> 00:19:30,586
[Vladimir breathing heavily]

386
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,296
[Vladimir snickers, grunts]

387
00:19:32,379 --> 00:19:34,882
[Vladimir snickers, in English]
Too strong, my little man.

388
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:38,427
[crowd cheering]

389
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:43,307
[intense music continues]

390
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:46,518
[crowd cheering]

391
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:52,357
- [in English] Let's go, let's go!
- [in English] Let's go!

392
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:54,985
- [intense music continues]
- [crowd cheering]

393
00:19:55,485 --> 00:19:56,320
‪[Vladimir laughs]

394
00:19:57,487 --> 00:19:58,405
[thuds]

395
00:19:58,488 --> 00:20:01,283
[crowd cheering]

396
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:03,368
[tense dramatic music playing]

397
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:05,829
[crowd cheering]

398
00:20:10,626 --> 00:20:15,130
[upbeat club music playing]

399
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:24,681
Do you have a lighter?

400
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,850
Sir, my co-worker has it.

401
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:31,188
[tense music playing]

402
00:20:31,271 --> 00:20:32,689
It smells like cigarettes.

403
00:20:33,315 --> 00:20:34,358
Ah…

404
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:35,484
Where is he?

405
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:37,027
He's over there.

406
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:38,695
Smoking is prohibited here.

407
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:42,241
Only members are allowed.

408
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:45,744
[tense music continues]

409
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:47,329
Ah! Sir, excuse me.

410
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:52,376
[tense music continues]

411
00:20:53,293 --> 00:20:54,253
Come on!

412
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:56,630
[whimpers] I don't want to…

413
00:20:57,089 --> 00:20:58,090
Boss.

414
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:03,053
What do you want?!

415
00:21:04,012 --> 00:21:05,180
[in English] My dear.

416
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:06,348
[in English] Relax. [chuckles]

417
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,893
This energy, I like, I like!

418
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,688
That's really how she is, boss.

419
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:14,731
[Bebang scoffs]

420
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,233
[Bebang clicks tongue]

421
00:21:16,316 --> 00:21:17,442
Behave yourself!

422
00:21:21,488 --> 00:21:22,739
It's like…

423
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:27,035
It's like I want to have her
all to myself first.

424
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:28,161
Ah. [chuckles]

425
00:21:28,704 --> 00:21:29,579
Just come back later.

426
00:21:29,663 --> 00:21:30,622
- Okay?
- All right.

427
00:21:30,706 --> 00:21:32,291
- [Bebang] All right, boss.
- [Atoy] Huh?

428
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:33,333
- [Bebang] Thanks.
- [Atoy chuckles]

429
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:35,002
Don't make too much of a mess, okay?

430
00:21:35,085 --> 00:21:36,253
Psst, behave!

431
00:21:36,336 --> 00:21:39,047
[tense music continues]

432
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:43,093
You're all disgusting!

433
00:21:45,053 --> 00:21:46,555
Don't make a scene.

434
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:48,849
I'm Ibyang's friend.

435
00:21:51,601 --> 00:21:57,607
[stirring music playing]

436
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,193
I'm here to rescue you.

437
00:22:03,113 --> 00:22:04,239
Thank God!

438
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:07,451
I thought… they were
going to sell me tonight.

439
00:22:08,618 --> 00:22:10,704
I won't let that happen.

440
00:22:10,787 --> 00:22:12,039
Don't worry.

441
00:22:12,956 --> 00:22:18,420
[stirring music continues]

442
00:22:20,630 --> 00:22:22,507
[electronic blipping]

443
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:29,931
[tense music playing]

444
00:22:30,807 --> 00:22:32,017
[security] <i>Check all the members inside.</i>

445
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:34,603
Someone is using Chipper Arenas' card.

446
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:36,188
[grunting and groaning]

447
00:22:36,271 --> 00:22:39,107
[Tessie] <i>This is</i>
<i>the demon customer's fault!</i>

448
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:40,942
He messed with Darryl!

449
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:42,694
[woman] Let's avenge Darryl!

450
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:43,612
[clamoring, grunting]

451
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:45,197
[in English] The person
we're looking for is an imposter.

452
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:47,866
- [in English] There's the pesky old man!
- [woman] <i>What's happening?</i>

453
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:49,367
[Mongki] They're trying
to catch an impostor!

454
00:22:49,451 --> 00:22:50,911
Pretending to be a gold card member!

455
00:22:50,994 --> 00:22:53,330
- Let's run, Gavin, it's dangerous here!
- What about Dad?

456
00:22:53,413 --> 00:22:54,247
That's my brother.

457
00:22:54,331 --> 00:22:58,251
Didn't your parents teach you
to respect elders?

458
00:22:58,835 --> 00:23:00,378
After I'm done with you,
you'll really grow old.

459
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:01,379
Is that a promise?

460
00:23:01,463 --> 00:23:02,506
UP NEXT

461
00:23:02,589 --> 00:23:05,926
[intense music continues]

462
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:11,890
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
